---
import Layout from '../../layouts/PhotosSaverLayout.astro'

const title = 'Privacy Policy - Photos Saver'
const description =
  'Privacy Policy for Photos Saver, a Google Photos companion app by Anas Alqoyyum.'
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
    <header class="border-b border-stone-200 pb-5 dark:border-zinc-800">
      <h1
        class="text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-stone-950 dark:text-zinc-50"
      >
        Privacy Policy
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-stone-600 dark:text-zinc-400">
        Last updated: March 17, 2026
      </p>
    </header>

    <div
      class="mt-8 space-y-8 text-[15px] leading-7 text-stone-700 dark:text-zinc-300"
    >
      <section class="space-y-3">
        <p>
          This Privacy Policy explains how Photos Saver collects, uses, and
          stores information when you use the Photos Saver browser extension and
          its supporting backend service. Photos Saver is operated by Anas
          Alqoyyum.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2
          class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-stone-950 dark:text-zinc-50"
        >
          Information used by Photos Saver
        </h2>
        <p>
          Photos Saver only requests and processes the information needed to
          provide the upload flow.
        </p>
        <ul
          class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-5 marker:text-stone-400 dark:marker:text-zinc-600"
        >
          <li>
            Google account identity information, such as the Google user
            identifier returned during sign-in.
          </li>
          <li>
            Google OAuth tokens, including an encrypted refresh token stored by
            the backend so the app can request new access tokens when needed.
          </li>
          <li>
            Image upload data that you explicitly send, including the image
            payload, filename, source URL, content type, and optional page URL.
          </li>
          <li>
            Temporary session and auth records needed to complete sign-in and
            maintain an authenticated session.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2
          class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-stone-950 dark:text-zinc-50"
        >
          How information is used
        </h2>
        <ul
          class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-5 marker:text-stone-400 dark:marker:text-zinc-600"
        >
          <li>Authenticate you with Google.</li>
          <li>Upload images you choose to your Google Photos library.</li>
          <li>
            Maintain session continuity and keep the app working securely.
          </li>
          <li>Diagnose operational or security issues when needed.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2
          class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-stone-950 dark:text-zinc-50"
        >
          Storage and retention
        </h2>
        <p>
          Refresh tokens are encrypted at rest in the backend data store.
          Temporary auth state, exchange codes, and session records are stored
          only for the limited time required for sign-in and session management.
          Uploaded image data is handled for the purpose of completing the
          requested upload.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2
          class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-stone-950 dark:text-zinc-50"
        >
          Third-party services
        </h2>
        <p>
          Photos Saver relies on third-party infrastructure to operate,
          including:
        </p>
        <ul
          class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-5 marker:text-stone-400 dark:marker:text-zinc-600"
        >
          <li>Google APIs and Google Photos</li>
          <li>
            Cloudflare Workers, KV, and D1 for backend hosting and storage
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Those services may process data as required to provide their
          platforms. Their handling of data is governed by their own terms and
          privacy policies.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2
          class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-stone-950 dark:text-zinc-50"
        >
          Data sharing
        </h2>
        <p>
          Photos Saver does not sell personal data. Data is only shared with
          service providers or APIs involved in delivering the requested
          functionality.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2
          class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-stone-950 dark:text-zinc-50"
        >
          Your choices
        </h2>
        <p>
          You may stop using Photos Saver at any time. You may also revoke the
          app's Google access from your Google account settings, which may
          disable the service until you authenticate again.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2
          class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-stone-950 dark:text-zinc-50"
        >
          Contact
        </h2>
        <p>
          For questions about this policy, use the public contact links listed
          in the footer of this page.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>
